review: Needlessly expensive, highly pretentious! What is offered here that is not at other places, much cheaper and potentially better? Let us evaluate:1. User Experience: Self-serve -- this is a good practice, however, if a store employs self-service, it has to reconsider the costs borne by the users. Ambience: Nothing out of the world that is worth the prices. Very noisy environment!2. Additional Amenities: Wi-Fi? You are better off using your phone data. Wi-Fi bandwidth provided at Starbucks (in India) is pathetic. Moreover, all your activities online (most-likely) are being monitored by the service provider.3. A place to sit and relax? Forget it. What is more relaxing than your 8x10 bedroom with a cup of self-made ginger tea or coffee?4. People, get this! Starbucks coffee is not a date. Be a little more imaginative with your romantic choices.Anything else? Oh yes. Those naming choices for the items served. name: Crits Pick
review: This is the first Starbucks to open in Bangalore. The cafe is conveniently just a minute's walk from the Forum Mall, Koramangala (You need to exit the mall where you will see Bosh in front of the mall, there are two entrances to the Forum mall). I've given a 3/5 for a couple of reasons. One, the toilet facility is really small for a two storey cafe, you may have to wait in line to use it. Second thing to note is, the menu is missing a few drinks when you compare it to overseas Starbucks outlets. (For example, Chai Latte is off the menu throughout India apparently). Indians love Chai ! Free WiFi is available for customers for a limited time/data usage. That's a plus. Is the coffee overpriced ? name: Yasir
review:
I usually go here to work once or twice a week. Itâ€™s a great place to work from.Usually the place is not too crowded so you can peacefully work without much background noise disturbing you during meetings or so.When it comes to the staff and menu, itâ€™s just like any other Starbucks - staff is helpful and very polite; menu is a tad bit pricey but it is what it is!I personally love the Kenya blend. My go to order is a French press with this blend. Their Christmas blend (seasonal) is also quite nice. I like their nachos and freshly prepared sandwiches.I am also in love with their playlist. It was amazing. Had frappuccino, and as â€¦More

name: Prathik R
review: There's a different air about a Starbucks. Most middle class folks (including myself) don't get it. Basically it's just another cafe, but mainly for those that want that extra special touch, i.e going the extra mile. Allow me to elaborate:I spent an entire day working here, from breakfast to dinner. Fast free wifi, ample charging spots, chill atmosphere, soothing ambient music.The freshly prepared sandwiches are fantastic, and the croissants just melts in your mouth. Coffee is same as most cafes, but the staff is quite knowledgeable about a customers intricate requirements.The staff welcomes everyone and bids bye as well, which i found endearing. On the day i went, they even gave the entire cafe a free cake slice sample coz they're trying out a new flavour apparently. The guy taking my order went over and beyond to tailor make my coffee just the way i wanted it, even giving me a few suggestions to suit my taste buds. (I basically suggested requirements which i thought matched a macchiato but apparently a costada was more suiting for me, it wasn't on the menu, but they still made it).Minor things that can be improved: Wooden seating is fine but man does it pain after a while of sitting. Ac is super strong, sends you to the ice age.Vegetarian options: Separate sectionParking: Only few parking for cars but ample for two wheelerWheelchair accessibility: There's outdoor seating which is accessibility friendlyFood: 5/5  |  Service: 5/5  |  Atmosphere: 5/5There's a different air about a Starbucks. Most middle class folks (including myself) don't get it. Basically it's just another cafe, but mainly for those that want that extra special touch, i.e going the extra mile. name: Peter Paul
review: Well located great space to work out of near vega city.Ambience: (4/5)Quite similar to most other Starbucks outlets, this one does not change things up too much. The only aspect of this space is that it seems to be more of a functional space where more people come and work given by the number of smaller tables that are in the space. There is also seating outside.Food/Coffee: (3/5)The black coffee was good, but I usually come to a Starbucks for the great work space than the coffee. But nonetheless the black coffee was well made. The cake and sandwiches were also decent.Summary: (3/5)Great functional space to work out of with a decent coffee. name: Anandita Kar

name: Prashant Jain
review: I am a coffee lover and I do go to lot of coffee shops including Tata Starbucks. Also, I am a gold member of Tata Starbucks. I visited this store today. I was hungry so I ordered the food also along with coffee. They have given me an option to order one more food item to get 50% discount. At first, I didn’t want to buy one more food item. Then I thought to avail the offer thinking it is Tata Starbucks and the food quality is good here. So I decided to buy one more food item thinking I am going to try something new from the menu. When I received my order I realized that I was cheated in the name of 50% discount. The food was so bad, I couldn’t even finish it. The food was stale. It wasn’t fresh at all. It looked like it was prepared couple of days ago. It was smelly and tasted like hell. I paid good amount of money for the order (for fresh food) but what I got was rubbish.  I didn’t expect that. I finished my coffee and ran away from the store. Later, I was thinking what else I could do with that amount of money. I was thinking, was it really Tata Starbucks? The two big brand names in the world are selling rubbish in India. This would be an end of my membership with Tata Starbucks.
